<subSubSection pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
This taxon is a narrow endemic of the central Andes of Chile and Argentina (
<bibRefCitation author="Giussani, L" journalOrPublisher="Australian Systematic Botany" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="B19" refString="Giussani, L, Anton, AM, Negritto, MA, Romanutti, AA, Soreng, RJ, 2012. Poa L. In: Zuloaga FO, Morrone O, et al. (Eds) Flora Argentina 3(2): 284-389." title="Poa L. In: Zuloaga FO, Morrone O, et al. (Eds) Flora Argentina 3 (2): 284 - 389." year="2012">Giussani et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Reports from Mexico by Hitchcock to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="DÃ¡vila">Davila</normalizedToken>
Aranda, from 1913 to 2006, as 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villaroellii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Poa villaroellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Clayton, WD" journalOrPublisher="Euphytica" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" publicationUrl="http://www.kew.org/data/grasses-db.html" refId="B8" refString="Clayton, WD, Vorontsova, MS, Harman, KT, Williamson, H, 2006. GrassBase - The Online World Grass Flora. http://www.kew.org/data/grasses-db.html" title="GrassBase - The Online World Grass Flora." url="http://www.kew.org/data/grasses-db.html" year="2006">Clayton et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acinaciphylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Poa acinaciphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are based on the specimens here referred to 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chamaeclinos">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Poa chamaeclinos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
